## The Argument

FUTON3 turns messy activity into organised knowledge by checking work against
shared patterns and producing auditable records. The system now operates across
four repos at three timescales:

- **Social (real-time)**: futon3c — agency, peripherals, evidence landscape,
  transport. 614 tests. 11 peripherals route agents through capability envelopes
  with hop-based transitions and evidence emission at every step.
- **Task (fast)**: futon3b — gate pipeline (G5→G0) produces typed proof-paths;
  Level 1 canonicalizer observes tensions and writes new patterns (Baldwin cycle).
- **Glacial (slow)**: futon3a — pattern similarity field (GloVe/fastText/MiniLM
  embeddings). Pending integration into G3 pattern selection.

The canonical pattern library lives in futon3/library/. The evidence landscape
(futon3c + futon1a XTDB backend) is the shared medium: social coordination
events, mission snapshots, PSR/PUR/PAR records, and portfolio observations all
flow into queryable evidence entries with reply chains and thread projections.

## Four-Repo Split (Evidence-Based)

As of 2026-02-18 the original "futon3" scope is implemented as:

- futon3  = canonical pattern library + devmaps (storage dependency; legacy runtime code mostly frozen)
- futon3a = query + similarity field (pattern indexing / portal / compass)
- futon3b = task coordination boundary (G5→G0) + glacial loop (L1 observe/canon)
- futon3c = social/realtime coordination layer (the most active repo: 614 tests,
  11 peripherals, evidence landscape, agency, transport, mission + mission-control systems)

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[holes/war-room.md (WR-1/WR-2 define the split and canonical library location)]
    evidence[library/coordination/ARGUMENT.flexiarg (gate pipeline argument)]
    evidence[library/realtime/*.flexiarg (social/realtime pattern set for futon3c)]
    evidence[futon3b/AGENTS.md Phase 0-3 verification + test tables]
    evidence[futon3b: L1 canonicalizer operational; rejection proof-paths typed; bootstrap closure complete]
    evidence[futon3c: 614 tests, 1996 assertions; 11 peripherals (10 wired); evidence landscape with XTDB]
    evidence[futon3c: alleycat verification 4/5 gates PASS (P-4 inhabitation, P-6 structural closure)]
    evidence[futon3c/holes/qa/implementation-inventory.md tracks component status]


