  + context: futon3c needs its own transport layer for real-time agent coordination, independent of the legacy futon3 MUSN transport.
  + IF: You want real-time agent coordination across multiple transports (HTTP, WebSocket, IRC)
  + HOWEVER: The legacy futon3 MUSN transport is a monolith that bundles pattern checking with transport
  + THEN: Implement independent transport adapters (HTTP, WebSocket, IRC) with a shared protocol layer, health endpoints, and event routing across transport boundaries
  + BECAUSE: Transport independence lets futon3c evolve its real-time coordination without depending on the legacy MUSN codebase

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon3c/src/futon3c/transport/protocol.clj: wire protocol shapes (~500 lines, 31 tests)]
    evidence[holes/completed-mission-summaries.md: M-IRC-stability — six failure-mode hardening pass that stabilized always-on IRC transport]
