! instantiated-by: Prototype 16 — Mission System [🔃/本 🌽/末]
  :maturity :active
  :owner :futon3c
  :actual-status :active
  :depends-on [f3/P13, f3/P14]
  :implemented-as [futon3c/src/futon3c/peripheral/{mission,mission_control,mission_control_backend,mission_control_shapes}.clj]
  :evidence-for-active [Mission peripheral: cycle machine with 9 phases, obligation tracking, evidence snapshots; Mission control: portfolio observation with cross-repo inventory, devmap coverage, mana queries; 35 mission-control tests + mission tests; full derivation xenotype complete for both]

  + context: Individual missions follow a development cycle (observe → propose → execute → validate); the portfolio of missions needs observation and prioritization.
  + IF: You want structured mission lifecycle management and portfolio-level visibility
  + HOWEVER: Without mission tooling, mission state lives in prose headers and hand-maintained inventories
  + THEN: Implement two peripherals: (1) mission peripheral — 9-phase cycle machine with obligation tracking, evidence emission on state changes, and phase gate enforcement; (2) mission-control peripheral — flat tool dispatch for cross-repo inventory scanning, devmap structural summaries, coverage analysis, mana queries, and portfolio review
  + BECAUSE: The mission peripheral makes individual mission state structural and evidence-backed; mission control makes portfolio state queryable and computable

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon3c/src/futon3c/peripheral/mission.clj: cycle machine, phase gates, obligation tracking]
    evidence[holes/completed-mission-summaries.md: M-mission-peripheral — generalized mission cycle machine (9 phases, obligation ledger, snapshots)]
    evidence[holes/completed-mission-summaries.md: M-mission-control — portfolio observation layer (inventory, coverage, review/backfill tooling)]
    evidence[holes/completed-mission-summaries.md: M-operational-readiness — overnight reliability gates for unattended mission execution]
    evidence[holes/completed-mission-summaries.md: M-portfolio-inference — AIF-style portfolio inference on top of mission-control observations]
    evidence[futon3c/src/futon3c/peripheral/mission_control.clj: portfolio observation peripheral]
    evidence[futon3c/src/futon3c/peripheral/mission_control_backend.clj: inventory, devmaps, coverage, mana, backfill]
    evidence[futon3c/holes/missions/M-mission-peripheral.md: INSTANTIATE complete]
    evidence[futon3c/holes/missions/M-mission-control.md: INSTANTIATE complete (35 tests, 614 suite)]
    evidence[Cross-repo scanning: 25 missions across futon3c (15 .md), futon3b (1 .md), futon5 (9 EDN devmaps)]
    evidence[Devmap coverage: heuristic name-matching (gap G1 documented, proper annotations future work)]
    evidence[D7 backfill: legacy missions convertible to evidence entries]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Run first real portfolio review and emit as evidence]
    next[Backfill legacy missions into evidence landscape]
    next[Add :query/subject-type filter to evidence store for "all missions" queries (gap G4)]
    next[Improve coverage heuristic with explicit devmap-to-mission annotations (gap G1)]

  :success-criteria
    pass[Mission peripheral manages lifecycle with phase gates and obligation tracking]
    pass[Mission control scans 4 repos and produces coherent portfolio review]
    pass[Portfolio reviews emittable as evidence entries]
    pass[Devmap coverage computable (even if heuristic)]
